official_title: A Randomized Trial Comparing the Effectiveness of Pre-test Genetic Counseling Using an Artificial Intelligence Program and Traditional In-person Genetic Counseling in Women Newly Diagnosed With Breast Cancer Who do Not Currently Meet National Comprehensive Cancer Network (NCCN) Criteria for Genetic Testing.
inclusion_criteria:
* Subjects diagnosed with Stage 0-3 breast cancer.
* Patients who do not satisfy current NCCN criteria for referral to a genetics counselor and genetics testing.
* Must have the ability to understand and the willingness to sign a written informed consent document as well as complete the study questionnaires.
Healthy volunteers allowed
Must be FEMALE
Must have minimum age of 18 Years
